tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  17,77,"the wont of those We sent before thee of Our Messengers; thou wilt find no change to Our wont."
  17,78,"Perform the prayer at the sinking of the sun to the darkening of the night and the recital of dawn; surely the recital of dawn is witnessed."
  17,84,"Say: 'Every man works according to his own manner; but your Lord knows very well what man is best guided as to the way.'"
  17,85,"They will question thee concerning the Spirit. Say: 'The Spirit is of the bidding of my Lord. You have been given of knowledge nothing except a little.'"